    "body": "Currently, using `ActionFuture#actionGet` will cause an `ElasticSearchException` to be thrown, but, it can be wrapped, for example, with a `RemoteTransportException`. The wrapping can be important, as it provides a \"trace\" to the origin of the failure.\n\nWe can automatically unwrap to the actual failure when throwing a failure from `actionGet`, and add to `ActionFuture` a helper method called `getRootFailure` which provides the actual (possibly wrapped) exception.\n", 
